Definite articles with places

We can leave out the definite article the when we talk about certain places.

Countries: Mexico, Colombia
(But we use the for the People's Republic of China, the United States of America, the United Kingdom)

Cities: New York City, Beijing, London
(But we use the when we say the city of London)

Towns: Springfield, Newbury

Stations: Grand Central Station

Streets: New Street

Lakes: Lake Como
